I believe items.concat([children]) is creating new components, therefor you will also need to pass `items` state down to the items components during the loop and again down then down `move(items, ...)` and `delete(items, ...)` methods so that they have the updated state on each render. 
**This will work but it&#39;s probably not best practice (code still at bottom of answer)**

[**Updated Answer**]

Either convert to a class based component which will allow you to be explicit with binding `this` or use a `renderItems` method to generate content without creating new components (shown in my snippet below)

Avoid mutating state array with [...items] where appropriate.

Dynamically generated content (such as with a loop or map) needs to have a a unique key prop for each item generated. Here I used `Math.random()` (which may not be suitable for production) 

You are also checking `futureIndex &lt; items.length -1` and it should be `futureIndex &lt; items.length` 

I&#39;ve created a working simplified/reworked example in JSX that may help you get where you need to go:

**UPDATED Snippet using `renderItems`**

&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: true --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-js --&gt;

    const PriorizationList = () =&gt; {
        const [items, setItems] = React.useState([]);
        
        const move = (currentIndex, futureIndex) =&gt; {
            if (futureIndex !== -1 &amp;&amp; futureIndex &lt; items.length ) {
                const tempItemsAray = [...items]
                const item = tempItemsAray[currentIndex];
                const movingItem = tempItemsAray[futureIndex];
                tempItemsAray[currentIndex] = movingItem;
                tempItemsAray[futureIndex] = item;
                setItems(tempItemsAray);
            }
        };
        const deleteItem = (index) =&gt; {
            setItems(prevItems =&gt; prevItems.filter((_,i) =&gt; i !== index));
        };
        const addItem = () =&gt; {
            const id = String(Math.floor(Math.random() * 100000))
            const newItems = [...items , { id }];
            setItems(newItems);
        };

        const renderItems = () =&gt; {
            return items.map((item, index) =&gt; {
                return (
                    &lt;div&gt;
                        &lt;span&gt;hi {item.id}&lt;/span&gt;
                        &lt;span&gt;
                            &lt;button type=&quot;pushUp&quot; onClick={() =&gt; move(index, index - 1)} &gt;up&lt;/button&gt;
                            &lt;button type=&quot;pushDown&quot; onClick={() =&gt; move(index, index + 1)} &gt;down&lt;/button&gt;
                            &lt;button type=&quot;delete&quot; onClick={() =&gt; deleteItem(index)} &gt;delete&lt;/button&gt;
                        &lt;/span&gt;
                    &lt;/div&gt;
                );
            }) 
        }

        return (
            &lt;div&gt;
                {renderItems()}
                &lt;button type=&quot;text&quot; onClick={addItem} &gt;
                    Add
                &lt;/button&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
        );
    };

    ReactDOM.render(
        &lt;PriorizationList /&gt;,
        document.getElementById(&quot;react&quot;)
    );

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;script src=&quot;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/react/16.8.4/umd/react.production.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;
        &lt;script src=&quot;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/react-dom/16.8.4/umd/react-dom.production.min.js&quot;&gt;&lt;/script&gt;

    &lt;div id=&quot;react&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;


&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;



